<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for loop uses the variable 'len' (declared as ssize_t) in its third clause: for (off = 0; off < sizeof(rand_data); off += (size_t) len). 'len' is assigned inside the loop body (len = read(...)), so the third clause uses an object that is modified by the loop body. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 (clause 3: the third clause shall modify only the loop counter and shall not use objects that are modified in the loop body).
</scenario>

